 began a family line that produced Oren Root (born 1803) and then Elihu Root (born 1845) — Secretary of War under President McKinley, Secretary of State under Theodore Roosevelt, and winner of the Nobel Peace Prize in 1912 for his work in international arbitration. When James Root then married Abigail Hooker as his second wife in 1793, he connected his family to the descendants of Rev. Thomas Hooker — meaning the Pixley-Hooker family and the Elihu Root line share a common progenitor in James Root, though the Nobel laureate descended from Lydia Robb's branch and carries no Hooker blood."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Edward Hooker, Descendants of Rev. Thomas Hooker (1909)","url":"https://archive.org/details/descendantsofrev00hook"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"james-root-1747"},"H00486":{"id":"H00486","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":6,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1753,"month":11,"day":30,"city":"Woodbury","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"H00254","mother_id":"I00162"},"tags":[],"sources":[{"label":"Edward Hooker, Descendants of Rev. Thomas Hooker (1909)","url":"https://archive.org/details/descendantsofrev00hook"},{"label":"Pixley Family Genealogy","url":"https://www.seekingmyroots.com/members/files/G005299.pdf"},{"label":"FindAGrave","url":"https://www.findagrave.com"}],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":2,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00984","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1790,"children_ids":["H01260","H01261","H01262","H01263","H01264"]},{"marriage_number":2,"spouse_id":"I00985","date_year":1793,"date_month":3,"date_day":2,"location_country":"United States","children_ids":["H01265"]}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"death":{"year":1841,"month":1,"day":6,"city":"Henrietta","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Abigail Hooker","first_name":"Abigail","maiden_name":"Hooker","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM497","plot_notes":"Maplewood Cemetery Henrietta Monroe County NY per FA"},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"character","header":"Outlived two husbands; died at Henrietta at eighty-seven","body":"Abigail Hooker Pixley buried her first husband Isaac Pixley in 1790 when she was thirty-six — left with six children, the youngest barely two — remarried James Root in 1793, bore another child, then buried Root in 1802 when she was forty-eight, and spent the next thirty-nine years a widow in Henrietta, New York, dying on January 6, 1841 at age eighty-seven. She had migrated from Woodbury, Connecticut to the Berkshire hills of Massachusetts as a young wife, and then west again to upstate New York as an old widow, the arc of her life tracking the westward movement of her entire generation — and she outlived every chapter of it, the Puritan inheritance carried through two husbands, seven children, and eighty-seven years."}],"slug":"abigail-hooker-1753"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}